<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head><meta charset="utf-8"><meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"><title>Contractor-vetting checklist</title></head>
<body style="margin:0;padding:0;background-color:#ffffff;font-family:-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,'Segoe UI',Roboto,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;color:#27272a;">
  <div style="max-width:600px;margin:0 auto;padding:32px 20px;">
    <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.65;margin:0 0 16px 0;">Hey,</p>
    <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.65;margin:0 0 16px 0;">Four weeks since you ran the calculator. You now have the sizing, system-type options, efficiency math, and rebate lookup. The last move is bids in front of you.</p>
    <h2 style="font-size:17px;color:#18181b;margin:28px 0 10px 0;">Before scheduling</h2>
    <ul style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.7;margin:0 0 18px 24px;padding:0;">
      <li>Check the state license database for current status and the right work scope.</li>
      <li>Look for complaint patterns, not just a star rating.</li>
      <li>Read recent local reviews, especially from homes similar to yours.</li>
    </ul>
    <h2 style="font-size:17px;color:#18181b;margin:28px 0 10px 0;">Get three quotes</h2>
    <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.65;margin:0 0 16px 0;">One quote is a vibe. Two is a coin flip. Three is a real comparison.</p>
    <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.65;margin:0 0 12px 0;">A serious quote should include: permit handling, specific model numbers, refrigerant type, ductwork scope, parts and labor warranty, commissioning, old-system disposal, electrical work, zoning if relevant, and a labor/equipment breakdown.</p>
    <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.65;margin:0 0 18px 0;">When two quotes are within 5% on price, do not pick on price. Pick on warranty, timeline, reputation, and what is included.</p>
    <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.65;margin:0 0 24px 0;"><a href="{{ cta_url }}" style="color:#FF6B2B;font-weight:600;text-decoration:underline;">Get quotes from local HVAC pros</a></p>
    <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.65;margin:0;">That is the sequence. Good luck with the install, and keep every certificate, invoice, and model number after you sign.</p>
    <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.65;margin:20px 0 4px 0;">&mdash; NailTheQuote</p>
